A massive ancient stone labyrinth viewed from above in warm sepia tones, with two distinct paths winding toward the center — one path is rushed and direct but crumbling with broken stones and dead ends, while the other path is longer, methodical, and solidly constructed with carefully placed cobblestones. Tiny figures in vintage 1900s attire walk both paths. The scene is rendered in a vintage cartographic illustration style, reminiscent of aged parchment maps with hand-drawn crosshatching and subtle coffee stains at the edges. Dramatic afternoon light casts long shadows across the maze walls, emphasizing the contrast between the hasty shortcuts and the deliberate proper route.
